################################################################
To create a recovery catalog, perform the following three steps:
################################################################
1. Configure the database in which you want to store the recovery catalog.
2. Create recovery catalog owner.
3. Create the recovery catalog.
SQL> create tablespace ts_rcat datafile '/orahome/app/oracle/oradata/db1/ts_rcat01.dbf' size 125m autoextend on;
SQL> create user rcat identified by rcat default tablespace ts_rcat quota unlimited on ts_rcat;
SQL> grant recovery_catalog_owner to rcat;
4. Go to the listener.ora add the entry for the sid for catalog is set and open that port in firewall range(1521-1524)
5. Go to the tnsnames.ora Make the entry for the same sid
6. Create dblink for catalog user and connect to the catalog 
7. [oracle@dw ~]$ rman catalog rcat/rcat@db1 ---> name in tnsnames.ora
− Execute the CREATE CATALOG command:
RMAN> create catalog;
8.− The database must be in the MOUNT or OPEN state to be successfully
registered.
− Using following command you can register the target database:
[oracle@dw ~]$ export ORACLE_SID=db2
[oracle@dw ~]$ rman catalog rcat/rcat@db1
RMAN> connect target /
RMAN> register database;
RMAN> list backup;
RMAN> catalog backuppiece 'file_name';
